Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
All blood parameters are within normal limits except for a mildly elevated platelet distribution width, which may indicate increased platelet size variability but is nonspecific. Urine is unremarkable except for a low specific gravity, possibly reflecting dilute urine or overhydration. No evidence of infection, anemia, renal dysfunction, or metabolic disturbance. Overall, results are largely unremarkable; clinical correlation is advised.
